The paper proposes a new approach for modeling structured data using Graphical Generative Adversarial Networks (Graphical-GAN). This involves combining the power of Bayesian networks and generative adversarial networks. The paper also introduces a structured recognition model to infer the posterior distribution of latent variables given observations. The proposed approach is evaluated on visual datasets, indicating a likely fit with the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning)
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence)
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition)
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing)
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks)
